data.value: The 2015 Nissan Altima stands as a reliable and stylish midsize sedan, offering a blend of performance and comfort. Under the hood, it boasts a 2.5-liter 4-cylinder engine, delivering a respectable 182 horsepower and providing ample power for daily driving needs. Paired with a smooth and efficient continuously variable transmission (CVT), the Altima delivers a balanced combination of power and fuel efficiency, achieving an EPA-estimated 27 mpg in the city and 38 mpg on the highway. Its exterior features sleek lines and available 17-inch alloy wheels, giving it a sophisticated look. Inside, the Altima offers a comfortable cabin with spacious seating and user-friendly controls. Technology features include a 5-inch color display audio system and Bluetooth connectivity for hands-free calling and audio streaming. Advanced safety features, such as antilock brakes, stability control, and Nissan's Advanced Air Bag System, provide peace of mind on the road. With a mileage of 38,000 miles and a price of $13,000, the 2015 Nissan Altima presents a compelling value proposition, combining affordability, reliability, and style for discerning drivers.
